I saw it was an O’Reilly book, I knew I was be able to access it through Safari Books Online.  If the overview below looks interesting, check it out at <a href=\"http://techbus.safaribooksonline.com/book/software-engineering-and-development/9781491965962\">Production-Ready Microservices: Safari Books Online - Premium</a> </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>One of the biggest challenges for organizations that have adopted microservice architecture is the lack of architectural, operational, and organizational standardization. After splitting a monolithic application or building a microservice ecosystem from scratch, many engineers are left wondering what’s next. In this practical book, author Susan Fowler presents a set of microservice standards in depth, drawing from her experience standardizing over a thousand microservices at Uber. You’ll learn how to design microservices that are stable, reliable, scalable, fault tolerant, performant, monitored, documented, and prepared for any catastrophe.</p>\n</blockquote>","frontmatter":{"title":"Production-Ready Microservices by Susan J. Fowler","description":null,"date":"February 6, 2017","tags":["microservices","architecture"],"canonical":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2017-02-06-production-ready-microservices-by-susan-j-fowler/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2017-01-28-profile-picture-performance-problems-pondered/"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["webdev","ux","caching"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2017-02-14-web-browser-secure-contexts/"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["webdev","security"]}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2589769190","97908498"],"slicesMap":{}}